HEADWORD: Miserably
<hw>Mis"er*a*bly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a miserable; unhappily;
calamitously; wretchedly; meanly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They were <qex>miserably</qex> entertained.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P.
Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fifth was <qex>miserably</qex> stabbed to death.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miseration</ent>⟦br⟧
